item.title: CVE-2017-1130|2024-09-16T21:58:13.936Z -- ibm -- notes
item.description: IBM Notes 8.5 and 9.0 is vulnerable to a denial of service. If a user is persuaded to click on a malicious link, it would open up many file select dialog boxes which would cause the client hang and have to be restarted. IBM X-Force ID: 121371.

item.title: CVE-2018-1437|2024-09-16T19:46:06.111Z -- ibm -- notes
item.description: IBM Notes 8.5 and 9.0 could allow an attacker to execute arbitrary code on the system, caused by an error related to multiple untrusted search path. A local attacker could exploit this vulnerability to DLL hijacking to execute arbitrary code on the system or cause the application to crash. IBM X-Force ID: 139565.
